-- в”Ђв”Ђ Sentry в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Application monitoring platform that gives developers real-time error tracking, distributed tracing, and session replay to find and fix production issues faster.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Usage-based subscription with a free developer tier$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free tier available; Team plan from $26/month billed annually$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2012, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$201-500 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Sentry Review 2026: Pricing, Features and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Sentry is a developer-focused error tracking and performance monitoring platform. See 2026 pricing plans, features, pros and cons, and top alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Sentry, operated by Functional Software, Inc., is an application monitoring platform founded in 2012 and headquartered in San Francisco, California. The company employs roughly 200 to 500 people across offices worldwide and has grown from a small open-source side project into one of the most widely adopted error-tracking and performance-monitoring tools for software teams. Sentry's product captures unhandled exceptions, stack traces, distributed traces, session replays, logs, and performance metrics across dozens of supported languages and frameworks, including JavaScript, Python, Node.js, Java, PHP, Ruby, Go, and mobile platforms like iOS and Android. Its core value proposition is helping engineering teams detect, triage, and resolve production issues before they affect large numbers of users, with features such as issue grouping, release tracking, source-map-based stack trace resolution, and an AI debugging agent called Seer that suggests root causes and fixes. Sentry offers four pricing tiers on sentry.io: a free Developer plan with 5,000 errors per month and one user, a Team plan starting at $26 per month billed annually, a Business plan starting at $80 per month billed annually, and a custom-priced Enterprise plan with dedicated support, SAML and SCIM support, and extended data retention. Pricing scales with usage across errors, trace spans, session replays, and log volume, with reserved-capacity discounts of roughly 20 percent versus pay-as-you-go rates. Sentry remains privately held and is commonly evaluated alongside tools like Datadog, New Relic, and Rollbar.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'dcce3938-3a1a-4634-a545-31842a7651dc';

