-- в”Ђв”Ђ ServiceNow в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Publicly traded enterprise cloud platform for IT service management, IT operations, HR, customer service, and security workflows, built on the Now Platform.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Custom quote-based subscription combining role-based and consumption-based licensing across product lines$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom quote only; no published list pricing$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2004, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$10,001+ employees (approximately 27,000-33,000 as of 2026; publicly traded, NYSE: NOW)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Santa Clara, California, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$ServiceNow Review 2026: Pricing, Features and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$ServiceNow is an enterprise IT service management and workflow automation platform. See 2026 pricing structure, key features, pros and cons, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$ServiceNow, Inc. (NYSE: NOW) is a publicly traded enterprise software company founded by Fred Luddy in June 2004 and headquartered in Santa Clara, California. As of 2026 the company employs roughly 27,000 to 33,000 people worldwide depending on the source and reporting period, and generates over 14 billion dollars in trailing twelve-month revenue with a market capitalization exceeding 100 billion dollars. ServiceNow's core product is the Now Platform, a low-code cloud platform that underpins a broad portfolio of workflow automation products including IT Service Management (ITSM), IT Operations Management (ITOM), Security Operations (SecOps), HR Service Delivery (HRSD), Customer Service Management (CSM), and increasingly AI-native agentic automation capabilities. Rather than selling a single product, ServiceNow licenses customers by combining role-based subscriptions, such as fulfiller and requester or approver access, with product-line subscriptions for each solution area, plus consumption-based pricing for certain metered services such as Application Engine usage and AI agent skills. In 2026 the company restructured its ITSM packaging, retiring the older Standard, Professional, and Enterprise editions in favor of three cumulative AI-native tiers, Foundation, Advanced, and Prime, with third-party estimates placing per-fulfiller costs somewhere between roughly $70 and $200 or more per month depending on tier and modules. ServiceNow does not publish list pricing; every deal is quoted individually based on module mix, user counts, and contract term, and mid-market rollouts of around 50 fulfillers commonly range from $500,000 to $2 million in first-year cost once implementation, customization, and training are included. ServiceNow competes with Atlassian's Jira Service Management, BMC Helix, Ivanti, and Salesforce in the IT and enterprise service management space, and is a distinct, unrelated company from ServiceTitan, a field-service management platform built for trades businesses.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'dba954e7-42de-4597-adda-d2b1563a9303';

